The '''celestial equator''' formed one of the boundaries of the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outlands Region]] along with the [[Great Rift]].

==Behind the scenes==
The celestial equator featured in the [[opening crawl]] in the rough draft and first two drafts of the screenplay for the [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|original film]]. It was deleted in [[The Star Wars: From The Adventures of Luke Starkiller|the third draft]].

In the real world, the galactic equator is the middle of the galactic plane, splitting the galaxy in half like two plates. It is used in the galactic coordinate system as 0 degrees latitude.

